						</div>
						<div class="accordion-content answer">
							<p>
								

	<p>If you're experiencing your computer running slow, there are a few things you can do to <a href='https://www.avg.com/en/signal/ultimate-guide-to-speeding-up-and-cleaning-up-your-pc' class='signal-link ' data-cmp-name='cmp-signal-link-builder-test' 'target='_blank'>speed up and clean up your computer</a>.</p>
<p>First, you can try using a <a href="/en-us/download-thank-you.php?product=GSE-2019&amp;variant=755">PC cleaner tool</a> to help remove any unnecessary files or programs that may be slowing down your computer. This will help to free up space on your hard drive and improve performance.
</p>
<p>It's also important to <a href='https://www.avg.com/en/signal/bloatware-removal-tool' class='signal-link ' data-cmp-name='cmp-signal-link-builder-test' 'target='_blank'>get rid of bloatware</a>, which are pre-installed programs that you may not need or use. These can take up valuable space and resources on your computer, slowing it down.</p>
<p>You can also <a href='https://www.avg.com/en/signal/how-to-test-your-pc-for-performance-and-battery-life' class='signal-link ' data-cmp-name='cmp-signal-link-builder-test' 'target='_blank'>test your PC's performance and battery life</a> to identify any hardware or software issues that may be contributing to its slow speed and need to be addressed.</p>
