							<p>
								

	<p>If your PC is running slow, it could be due to outdated software and drivers, which affect the performance of your PC&rsquo;s hardware as well as audio and graphics quality. Be sure to check for and install any available updates to improve PC performance. Using a <a href="/en-us/avg-driver-updater">driver updater</a> can help ensure that all of your drivers are up to date. Other ways to <a href='https://www.avg.com/en/signal/ultimate-guide-to-speeding-up-and-cleaning-up-your-pc' class='signal-link ' data-cmp-name='cmp-signal-link-builder-test' 'target='_blank'>fix a slow computer</a> include disabling unnecessary startup programs, <a href='https://www.avg.com/en/signal/top-three-ways-to-clean-temporary-files-from-your-computer' class='signal-link ' data-cmp-name='cmp-signal-link-builder-test' 'target='_blank'>deleting temporary files</a>, and freeing up disk space.
</p>



							</p>
